article.headline: Texas A&amp,M 60, Sam Houston St. 50
article.story: COLLEGE STATION, Texas -- Chinemelu Elonu scored 11 points and had 11 rebounds to help Texas A&M win its seventh straight Sunday night with a 60-50 victory over Sam Houston State. B.J. Holmes came off the bench to add 11 points and Bryan Davis scored 10 and had three blocked shots for the Aggies (11-1). Ashton Mitchell scored 16 points to lead Sam Houston State (5-6). DeLuis Ramirez added 10. Texas A&M led throughout the game. The Aggies shot 41 percent from the field while Sam Houston State shot 33 percent.
